"{\"uid\": \"blueprint.ng-chiles-appeals-to-supreme-court-over-olympic-bronze\", \"entities\": [{\"sentence\": \"September 18, 2024Admin IIISports0  American gymnast Jordan Chiles has filed an appeal in the Federal Supreme Court of Switzerland after being denied a bronze medal in the women's floor event at the 2024 Olympics.\", \"from\": 0, \"to\": 213, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 36, \"end\": 44, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\", \"score\": 0.9999999997153282, \"rank\": 1.5155635295309754e-10, \"text\": \"American\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\"}, {\"begin\": 53, \"end\": 66, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Jordan_Chiles\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Jordan Chiles\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Jordan_Chiles\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Jordan_Chiles\"}, {\"begin\": 94, \"end\": 115, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Supreme_Court_of_the_United_States\", \"score\": 0.9893621922370794, \"rank\": 0.010751126723551056, \"text\": \"Federal Supreme Court\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Supreme_Court_of_the_United_States\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Supreme_Court_of_the_United_States\"}, {\"begin\": 119, \"end\": 130, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Switzerland\", \"score\": 0.9999999983933776, \"rank\": 1.6024559425844722e-09, \"text\": \"Switzerland\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Switzerland\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Switzerland\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"It is the latest appeal from Chiles, 23, who has already had two rejected by the Court of Arbitration for Sport (Cas).\", \"from\": 215, \"to\": 333, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Romania's Ana Barbosu was awarded bronze instead by the International Gymnastics Federation (Fig)following a Cas ruling.\", \"from\": 335, \"to\": 455, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 335, \"end\": 342, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Romania\", \"score\": 0.9993922702598005, \"rank\": 0.0006074050793612643, \"text\": \"Romania\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Romania\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Romania\"}, {\"begin\": 391, \"end\": 432, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/International_Gymnastics_Federation\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"International Gymnastics Federation (Fig)\", \"types\": [\"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/International_Gymnastics_Federation\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/International_Gymnastics_Federation\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Chiles had initially finished fifth but, after an inquiry with regard to the difficulty rating of her routine, officials upgraded her score to put her third.\", \"from\": 457, \"to\": 614, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"But Barbosu and her team then appealed to Cas that the inquiry had been registered four seconds after the one-minute deadline allowed by Fig.\", \"from\": 616, \"to\": 757, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Cas is usually deemed the highest level of sporting authority on all legal matters.\", \"from\": 759, \"to\": 842, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Reports in US media had suggested the head of the Cas panel making the decision in the case had links to Romania, with Cascondemning \\\"outrageous statements\\\"that it was biased.\", \"from\": 844, \"to\": 1019, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 855, \"end\": 857, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Federal_government_of_the_United_States\", \"score\": 0.727254726924835, \"rank\": 0.3749851518492691, \"text\": \"US\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Federal_government_of_the_United_States\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Federal_government_of_the_United_States\"}, {\"begin\": 949, \"end\": 956, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Romania\", \"score\": 0.9993922702598005, \"rank\": 0.0006074050793612643, \"text\": \"Romania\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Romania\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Romania\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Lawyers for Chiles argue that Cas refused to consider video footage that \\\"unequivocally proves\\\" that the inquiry was submitted in time.\", \"from\": 1021, \"to\": 1156, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Last month, Chiles said she receivedonline racist abuseafter the decision to strip her of the bronze medal.\", \"from\": 1158, \"to\": 1265, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Chiles won gold in the team event in Paris, as part of a US team that included Simone Biles.\", \"from\": 1267, \"to\": 1359, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1304, \"end\": 1309, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"score\": 0.9999991529988569, \"rank\": 8.470018879310788e-07, \"text\": \"Paris\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\"}, {\"begin\": 1324, \"end\": 1326, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Federal_government_of_the_United_States\", \"score\": 0.727254726924835, \"rank\": 0.3749851518492691, \"text\": \"US\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Federal_government_of_the_United_States\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Federal_government_of_the_United_States\"}, {\"begin\": 1346, \"end\": 1358, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Simone_Biles\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Simone Biles\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Simone_Biles\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Simone_Biles\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Scotland agrees to host Commonwealth Games in 2026  Lagos: Police confirm 54-year-old commits suicide by hanging  20212023 general